# Ignore everything by default; only re-included paths below ship in the .vsix.
# Note: vsce auto-expands any bare "!dirname" negate line into an additional
# "!dirname/**", so a bare "!node_modules" would silently re-include all of
# node_modules (openai/onnxruntime/etc). Only use "/**"-suffixed negate lines.
**

!dist/**
# media/demo.gif is intentionally excluded here -- it's only used in
# README.md, which vsce rewrites to a raw GitHub URL at publish time, so it
# doesn't need to ship in the installable package. Everything below is listed
# individually rather than as "!media/**" since re-excluding one file inside
# an already-negated directory doesn't reliably override the negation.
!media/icon.svg
!media/lance-db-explorer-logo.png
!media/shell.css
!media/icons/**
!package.json
!README.md
!LICENSE

# @lancedb/lancedb is external to the esbuild bundle (native bindings can't be
# bundled), so its JS glue and platform-specific binary package must ship as
# real node_modules. apache-arrow is required internally by lancedb at runtime.
# tslib and flatbuffers are apache-arrow's own runtime deps (required by its
# IPC/flatbuffer message parsing, not just its unused bin/arrow2csv CLI).
# reflect-metadata is required unconditionally by @lancedb/lancedb's index.js
# (it eagerly imports its embedding-function registry even though we never
# use it). Missing any of these doesn't fail the build -- esbuild only
# bundles code actually reachable from our own imports, so it silently
# succeeds, and the extension fails to activate at all once installed,
# since these are real requires inside lancedb/apache-arrow's own already-
# bundled JS. Everything else under node_modules (including lancedb's
# unused optional embedding integrations - openai, huggingface transformers,
# onnxruntime, and apache-arrow's own unused CLI deps - command-line-args,
# command-line-usage, json-bignum) stays excluded by the blanket "**" above.
!node_modules/@lancedb/**
!node_modules/apache-arrow/**
!node_modules/tslib/**
!node_modules/flatbuffers/**
!node_modules/reflect-metadata/**
